Bourbon Chile Barbecue Sauce

2 tbsp unsalted butter
2 garlic cloves, minced
½ small yellow onion, minced
1 red Thai chile—stemmed, seeded and minced
⅔ c ketchup
¼ c dark brown sugar
¼ c bourbon
2 tbsp apple cider vinegar
2 tbsp peach preserves
1 tbsp honey
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste

In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, onion and chile, and cook until lightly golden, 8 min. Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring often, until thickened, 15 min. Allow to cool completely before using to marinate or baste.
